The paper deals with multimedia streaming and privacy violations, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses eavesdropping on network traffic, which is a security concern and could place it in the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper uses machine learning algorithms for classification, which could place it in the categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the accuracy and robustness of the algorithms, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
